===Etymology===
For the Hokkien sense of "alleyway; alley; narrow street", possibly related to {{m|nan-hbl|間|tr=kàn|t=gap; partition}} or possibly a {{sl|nan-hbl|nl|gang|t=alleyway, alley, narrow street|nocap=1|nocat=1}} or from {{bor|nan-hbl|ms|pekan|nocat=1}}<ref>{{cite-journal|author=Lo Man Yuk|journal=Journal of the Straits Branch of the Royal Asiatic Society|title=Chinese Names of Streets in Penang|number=31-34|url=https://books.google.com.ph/books?id=rFMYAAAAYAAJ&pg=RA2-PA204&dq=kan+hokkien&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiahJbhp4iHAxUOslYBHRG1A1IQ6AF6BAgKEAI#v=onepage&q=kan%20hokkien&f=false|date=July 1898|publisher=American Mission Press|location=Singapore|page=204}}</ref> as a {{clipping|ms||nocap=1|nocat=1}}, but this term is also found recorded in the ''Dictionario Hispanico Sinicum'' (1626-1642) as ''"{{l|es|parián|Parian}} 墹 can̂."''<ref>{{R:Dictionario Hispanico Sinicum|728}}</ref> which is also read as {{l|nan-hbl|墹|tr=kàn}}.

